str2: Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.
A dog, universally despised in the East. A primary word; a dog.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Set apart by (or for) God, holy, sacred. From hagos; sacred.
And not, not even, neither?nor. From me and de; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: (a) I cast, throw, rush, (b) often, in the weaker sense: I place, put, drop. A primary verb; to throw.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
A pearl. From margaros; a pearl.
From en and pros; in front of (literally or figuratively) or time).
A swine, hog, sow. Of uncertain derivation; a hog.
When, at what time. From the base of pou and te; interrogative adverb, at what time.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: From kata and pateo; to trample down; figuratively, to reject with disdain.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
The foot. A primary word; a 'foot'.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Passive - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: Strengthened from the base of trope; to twist, i.e. Turn quite around or reverse.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To rend, break asunder; I break forth (into speech); I throw or dash down.
